      "date": "2017-02-28 00:40:27.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1\n\n(1 comment)\n\nit's a workaround approach to fix this problem.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "72d9c9c9e47b61e4792c0e056c0b977e76a5800f",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 4,
        "name": "Jinshan Xiong",
        "email": "jinshan.xiong@intel.com",
        "username": "Jay",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2017-02-28 00:41:42.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nMy patch for prl_fs:\n\n[root@centos7 prl_mod]# cat patch \ndiff -pur prl_mod.orig/prl_fs/SharedFolders/Guest/Linux/prl_fs/file.c prl_mod/prl_fs/SharedFolders/Guest/Linux/prl_fs/file.c\n--- prl_mod.orig/prl_fs/SharedFolders/Guest/Linux/prl_fs/file.c\t2017-01-18 01:36:56.000000000 -0800\n+++ prl_mod/prl_fs/SharedFolders/Guest/Linux/prl_fs/file.c\t2017-02-16 08:01:57.027000000 -0800\n@@ -268,7 +268,38 @@ out:\n static ssize_t prlfs_read(struct file *filp, char *buf, size_t size,\n \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tloff_t *off)\n {\n-\treturn prlfs_rw(filp, buf, size, off, 0, 1, TG_REQ_COMMON);\n+\tint user = segment_eq(get_fs(), USER_DS);\n+\tchar *new_buf = buf;\n+\tsize_t bufsize = 1024 * 1024;\n+\tssize_t bytes_read = 0;\n+\n+\tDPRINTK(\"ENTER, user = %d\\n\", user);\n+\tif (user)\n+\t\treturn prlfs_rw(filp, buf, size, off, 0, user, TG_REQ_COMMON);\n+\n+\tnew_buf = kmalloc(bufsize, GFP_KERNEL);\n+\tif (new_buf == NULL)\n+\t\treturn -ENOMEM;\n+\n+\twhile (size > 0) {\n+\t\tssize_t res;\n+\n+\t\tres = prlfs_rw(filp, new_buf, bufsize < size ? bufsize : size, off, 0, user, TG_REQ_COMMON);\n+\t\tif (res == 0)\n+\t\t\tbreak;\n+\n+\t\tif (res < 0 && bytes_read == 0) {\n+\t\t\tbytes_read = res;\n+\t\t\tbreak;\n+\t\t}\n+\n+\t\tmemcpy(buf + bytes_read, new_buf, res);\n+\t\tbytes_read += res;\n+\t\tsize -= res;\n+\t}\n+\n+\tkfree(new_buf);\n+\treturn bytes_read;\n }\n \n #if LINUX_VERSION_CODE >= KERNEL_VERSION(4, 7, 0)\n@@ -294,9 +325,10 @@ static ssize_t prlfs_write(struct file *\n \tssize_t ret;\n \tstruct dentry *dentry = FILE_DENTRY(filp);\n \tstruct inode *inode = dentry->d_inode;\n+\tint user = segment_eq(get_fs(), USER_DS);\n \n \tprlfs_inode_lock(inode);\n-\tret = prlfs_rw(filp, (char *)buf, size, off, 1, 1, TG_REQ_COMMON);\n+\tret = prlfs_rw(filp, (char *)buf, size, off, 1, user, TG_REQ_COMMON);\n \tdentry->d_time = 0;\n \tif (ret < 0)\n \t\tgoto out;",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
